    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Those whose occupation is the preparation of plans and specifications related to the prevention of accidental deaths and injuries. The duties of a safety engineer may include the identification and appraisal of accident-producing conditions and practices and the development of accident control methods or systems.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
